#X text 430 660 <- click learn and then move the [knob] to the left (check the help file of [receiver] for more), f 50;
#X text 611 697 The name comes out the right outlet and can be used to set a receive name of another GUI or save with the patch with [savestate] or something., f 29;
#X msg 487 719 receive \$1 \, dirty;
#X text 18 23 In Vanilla \, when in edit mode \, [knob] shows its inlet and outlet \, but they are hidden in run mode. For PlugData they always show but you can hide them in presentation mode., f 57;
#X text 18 74 The inlet gets hidden if you have a receive symbol \, same with the outlet for a send symbol. A send symbol sends messages to a matching [receive] object. A receive symbol makes [send] objects communicate to it. If you set send/receive names to "empty" \, the symbols are cleared and inlet/outlet are shown (same if you give an actual 'empty' symbol). Note you need to escape dollar signs with backslashes to set send/receive names via messages or flags \, but not via properties!, f 57;
